File: Johannesburg Emergency Services is investigating the cause of the blaze which put over 200 people on the streets for hours. JOHANNESBURG - Residents of a Johannesburg block of flats had a lucky escape after a fire broke out in their building on Saturday. Johannesburg Emergency Services is investigating the cause of the blaze which put over 200 people on the streets for hours. They've since returned to their homes. Some say an electrical fault could be to blame. Scores of people have been displaced by a fire at a block of flats in downtown Johannesburg. The building caught alight this morning. Manqoba Mchunu has the report. Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/5ZIMxYLLfa